================================================================================
NOTICE — Third-Party Attribution
================================================================================

1. Hope2333/bun-termux — MIT License, Copyright (c) 2026 Hope2333
   https://github.com/Hope2333/bun-termux
   Scope: Upstream fork ancestry. Provided the initial pure-android packaging
   scaffolding (Makefile targets for deb/pacman, packaging/ layout, docs
   skeleton). This fork extends it with source-level Bun patches, an
   LD_PRELOAD shim (src/libbun-android-fix.c), TinyCC overlays, launcher
   scripts with network-fix, and full-FFI support.

2. Happ1ness-dev/bun-termux — MIT License, Copyright (c) 2026 Happ1ness-dev
   https://github.com/Happ1ness-dev/bun-termux
   Scope: Shim patterns in src/libbun-android-fix.c are adapted from their
   shim.c — specifically: safe_dir_fd EACCES-dup trick during directory
   resolver walk, /proc/stat synthesis via memfd_create, /etc/resolv.conf
   fopen redirect, execve shebang translation, /tmp → $TMPDIR mkdir/symlink
   translation, linkat EXDEV copyfile fallback, and __OPEN_NEEDS_MODE Bionic
   workaround. Their upstream uses userland-exec + glibc; this fork ports the
   patterns to Bionic-native LD_PRELOAD.

3. TinyCC (patches/tinycc/*.overlay) — LGPL-2.1
   https://repo.or.cz/tinycc.git
   Files tccrun.c and arm64-link.c are modifications of TinyCC upstream and
   remain under LGPL-2.1. Modifications: memfd_create for executable pages
   (Android SELinux) in tccrun.c; ARM64 veneer stub generation for
   out-of-range BL calls in arm64-link.c.

4. Bun — MIT License, Copyright (c) 2025 Oven, Inc.
   https://github.com/oven-sh/bun
   Zig source patches in this fork target Bun v1.3.14 and are contributed
   under Bun's MIT license.
